steps.instruction:
For a more step by step guide go [here](https://www.kingarthurflour.com/blog/2009/03/17/no-knead-bread-the-beat-goes-on)

1. Coarsely chop the pecans
2. Mix the fours, salt, yeast, and water in a large bowl
3. Stir then mix with your hands, make sure to incorporate all of the flour
4. Work in the fruits and nuts
5. Cover the bowl with plastic wrap
6. Let rest for 8 hours at room temp
7. After 8 hours, turn the dough out onto a lightly floured work surface
8. Form it into a log or a round loaf to fit in your 14" to 15" long lidded stoneware baker; 9"x12" oval deep casserole dish with cover; or 9" to 10" round lidded baking crock
9. Lightly grease whatever pan you're using 
10. Place the dough into the pan, smooth side up
11. Cover and let rest at room temp for about 2 hours
12. Using a sharp knife, slash bread in a crosshatch pattern
13. Put the lid on the pan
14. Put the pan in a cold oven
15. Set the oven to 450F
16. Bake the bread for 45 to 50 minutes
     - Start the timer when you put the bread in
17. Take off the top
18. Bake for another 5 to 15 minutes, until it's deep golden brown
19. Remove from oven
20. Allow to cool completely 

#### Tip
- Walnuts sometimes give this bread a faint purple tinge. If this bothers you, use pecans instead.
